<h1>Truncated differential cryptanalysis of five rounds of Salsa20</h1>
    
<p class="authors">
<strong><a href="../">Paul Crowley</a></strong></p>

<p class="cite">SASC 2006 workshop without proceedings</p>

<p class="abstract"><strong>Abstract.</strong>
We present an attack on Salsa20 reduced to five of its twenty rounds. This
attack uses many clusters of truncated differentials and requires 2^165
work and 2^6 plaintexts.</p>

